724630f-a.folder: West Street & North Moore Street, Manhattan, NY

724628f-a.title: Manhattan: West Street - North Moore Street
724628f-a.text:
(1)
West Street, south from North Moore Street, showing foundation work
for the southward extension (from Canal Street) of the West Side Express
Highway. For an account of same see, the New Aork Times of November
12, 1937. The buildings shown line the east side of this thoroughfare.
July 28, 1937.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.
(2)
Another view, two blocks southward. The photographers vantage
point is Harrison Street and shows between pile drivers the 29-storied
New York Telephone Building.
July 28, 1937.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.
Neg ~ 29G7

724627f-a.title: Manhattan: West Street - North Moore Street
724627f-a.text:
West Street, west side, at the foot of North Moore Street, showing
the newly constructed North River Pier No. 25.
August 2, 1937.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.
